title: Nonstopspider
author: Nonstopspider
content: Hello Guys,Yesterday $VGX, AKA the token of Voyager, was listed on Mexc Global Exchange, a sign of recovery after the announcement of the Binance acquisition (bah, better said, saving the protocol). At the same time still recovering slowly the price, and maybe, an initial trend to reach again the 1 USD. If BTC can brake the resistance, $VGX can be a good profit generator (obviously depending on what binance announces or what kind of action will take on this protocol.But What do you think of this new Listing of VGX? Can the protocol regain confidence or Binance will rebrand it or consume it?
